<chapter id="ch-requirements">
  <title>Requirements</title>
  <section id="sn-functional-requirements">
    <title>Functional Requirements</title>
    <para>
      A listing of functional software requirements for &GMOJO_APP;
    </para>

    <section id="project-files">
      <title>Project Files</title>
      <para>
        An entire project consists of the project file and all the data
        referenced by that file.
      </para>

      <para>
        The user should not have to name the project until saving.
      </para>

      <para>
        The user should not have to specify any directories to save data to
        when creating a new project.
      </para>

      <section id="project-file">
        <title>The Project File</title>
        <para>
          The project the file contains data aswell as references to the
          audio data on disk.
        </para>

        <variablelist>
          <title>Project File Requirements</title>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Human Readable</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                A project file should be human readable. why?
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
            <term>Able to be moved</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                The project file must be able to be moved and the project
                should still open.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
      </section>

